tile.description:
```glsl
vec2 tile(vec2 p, vec2 count [, out vec2 cellId])
```

Repeat-tile UVs by `count`. Optional `cellId` out-param gives integer cell coords for per-cell variation.
PERF: FREE — one fract + floor.

**Example:**
```glsl
vec2 cell;
vec2 q = tile(uv, vec2(4.0, 4.0), cell);
// q is [0,1] within each tile; cell.x in {0,1,2,3}
```

*Auto-imports* `/core/transform/tile.glsl`
